<p>Speaking by telephone from the Lithuanian capital of Vilnius, she said: 'I wish him to overcome his fears, look truth in the eye, listen to the voice of the people and go away.'</p>

<p>Mr Lukashenko has consistently blamed Western countries for encouraging the protests, and contends that Nato is repositioning forces along Belarus' western border with the aim of intervening in the unrest - a claim the alliance strongly denies.</p>

<p>The Belarusian Defence Ministry said on Sunday that it was conducting military exercises in the Grodno region, near the borders of Poland and Lithuania, simulating defending against an invasion.</p>

